    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="[21 June 2021, Cox's Bazar]Refugee: Currently, there are approximately 877,000 displaced Rohingya residing in camps in the Ukhiya and Teknaf Upazilas of Cox’s Bazar District (UNHCR, 2021). More than half of the refugees in the camp are children (Vince, 2020). There are thirty-four camps formally designated by the government of Bangladesh, including the two officially recognised camps, Kutupalong and Nayapara, as well as several camps supported by agencies such as the International Organis ation for Migration (IOM) and the UN Refugee Agency (UNHCR) (UNHCR, 2020; Banerjee, 2019; Milton et al, 2017). Along with existing challenges in addressing access to health services, food shortages and education needs (Pocock et al, 2017), the risks posed by waterrelated hazards for those living in the camps are high. Cox’s Bazar is a district that is prone to floods, storm surges and the seasonal monsoon impact, whilst the refugee camps and their surrounding areas are highly susceptible to flash flooding and rainfall triggered landslides (Banerjee, 2019; Ahmed, 2015)."/>
    <cas:View sofa="1" members="8 19 24 29 34 39 44 57 70 83 96 109 122 135 148 161 174 187 200 213 226 239 252 265 278 291 304 317 330 343 356 369 382 395 408 421 434 447 460 473 486 499 512 525 538 551 564 577 590 603 616 629 642 655 668 681 694 707 720 733 746 759 772 785 798 811 824 837 850 863 876 889 902 915 928 941 954 967 980 993 1006 1019 1032 1045 1058 1071 1084 1097 1110 1123 1136 1149 1162 1175 1188 1201 1214 1227 1240 1253 1266 1279 1292 1305 1318 1331 1344 1357 1370 1383 1396 1409 1422 1435 1448 1461 1474 1487 1500 1513 1526 1539 1552 1565 1578 1591 1604 1617 1630 1643 1656 1669 1682 1695 1708 1721 1734 1747 1760 1773 1786 1799 1812 1825 1838 1851 1864 1877 1890 1903 1916 1929 1942 1955 1968 1981 1994 2007 2020 2033 2046 2059 2072 2085 2098 2111 2124 2137 2150 2163 2176 2189 2202 2215 2228 2241 2254 2267 2280 2293 2306 2319 2332 2345 2358 2371 2384 2397 2410 2423 2436 2449 2462 2475 2488 2501 2514 2527 2540 2553 2566 2579 2592 2605 2618 2631 2644 2657 2670 2683 2696 2709 2722 2735 2748 2761 2779 2774 2791 2796 2815 2820 2825 2844 2856 2861 2873 2885 2890 2784 2801 2808 2830 2837 2849 2866 2878 2902 2895 2909 2916 2919 2912 2923 2936"/>
